Janet Yellen has been confirmed as the next Chair of the Federal Reserve, with bipartisan support. The President believes that Yellen will be a strong advocate for improving the lives and standard of living of American workers and their families. Yellen is a respected economist and has been a leading voice at the Fed for over a decade. She has been instrumental in pulling the economy out of recession and promoting steady growth. Yellen is committed to the Fed's dual mandate of keeping inflation in check and reducing unemployment. She also recognizes the importance of a stable financial system in supporting the overall economy and protecting consumers. The President is confident that Yellen will prioritize the interests of American workers, consumers, and the stability of the financial system, and help the economy continue to grow in the future.